<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4272919>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 203–206.Primary types of the Nearctic species of the Anthomyza macra group and their habitat. 203 – A. tenuis (Loew, 1863), lectotype male, laterally and its type labels, body length 2.74 mm; 204 – habitat of the Nearctic species of the A. macra group in Moosonee (Canada: Ontario); 205 – A. silvatica sp. nov., holotype male, laterally, body length 2.50 mm; 206 – A. oblonga sp. nov., holotype male, laterally, body length 2.65 mm. Photo by K. N. Barber (Fig. 204) and J. Roháček (others)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4272919/files/figure.png" .

